b'Meet Rene\xe2\x80\x99. b'Meet Selina. Selina Garrison has held numerous leadership positions over the course of her career. Her BS in Physics gives her the ability to understand technical challenges, and her studies in Quality allows her to recognize the importance of prioritizing the voice of the customer.  #Juneteenth'

b'Meet La Toya. La Toya T. Haynes is a strategic Human Resources professional who serves as an Ecosystem Business Partner and Global Co-Chair for our Intuit African Ancestry Network. She holds a Bachelor\xe2\x80\x99s degree in Business Management from Southern University and A&M College and a Master\xe2\x80\x99s degree in Organizational Development and Executive Coaching from the University of Texas. La Toya has over twenty years of professional experience and has been a member of the Intuit family for over three years. #Juneteenth'

b"Meet Damion. Damion Wright is a Senior Sales Leader with more than 15 years of combined experience in operational oversight, strategic sales and market planning, business process optimization, and focused, purposeful team and talent development. With a commitment to building culturally-positive environments, he has been able to create competitive advantage by leveraging his ability to build cohesive sales programs capable of boosting bottom-line profitability and organizational recognition.\nHe currently serves as a Senior Sales Leader, leading Intuit's Early Career and Diversity Programs across the US Sales Organization. Damion graduated from Colorado State University with a Master\xe2\x80\x99s Degree in Organizational Performance and Change and additionally holds a B.S. in Communications and Public Relations from Weber State University. Damion is the father of three beautiful daughters.#Juneteenth"

b'Meet Tia. Tia Bradley is the Intuit Accountants Partner Experience Delivery Leader and the Plano Site African Ancestry Chair. She has worked at Intuit for 15 years. She prides herself on being an excellent relationship builder and culture curator. Her passion is to inspire others to do their best work and bring joy to their lives. #Juneteenth'

b'Meet Rudy. With over 20 years of experience across several industries, Rudy PointduJour\xe2\x80\x99s passion is  to consistently deliver strong outcomes for Customers, Partners and business, which led him to Intuit. He feels blessed to lead the Intuit Partnerships in the Professional Tax Customer Success organization. Outside of Intuit, you can find him with his awesome wife, chasing their 20 month old daughter and traveling abroad or visiting family on the east coast.  #Juneteenth'

b'Meet Tanjanique.  Tanjanique Bradford is a service and support manager in Plano, Texas.  She is a Louisiana native who decided to make Texas her \xe2\x80\x9cHome Sweet Home.\xe2\x80\x9d She has been part of the Intuit family for 22 years and appreciates the business and life lessons she has encountered as an Intuit employee. Outside of work, she loves traveling and spending time with family and friends. #Juneteenth'

b'Meet Uche. Uche Anyanwu is a Customer Experience Leader and Intuit African Ancestry Network co-chair in San Diego, CA.  In her current role she advocates for the customer\xe2\x80\x99s voice to create new opportunities to deliver impactful customer experiences across different touch points in their financial journey. As someone born to parents who immigrated to the US, and as a believer in the democratization of tech careers for underserved communities, it\xe2\x80\x99s very personal to her to do everything she can to create space for inclusivity through financial education and most importantly community building. To do this, she believes that with a growth mindset, passion, and innovation, we can make the impossible happen.  #Juneteenth'

b'Meet Rahshad.  Rahshad Slocum is a Business Systems Analyst for Learning at Intuit. \xe2\x80\x9cAt this time in my life there\xe2\x80\x99s a sense of synergy. It\xe2\x80\x99s worldwide, it\xe2\x80\x99s visible, and it feels deliberate. It feels finally real. I remember feeling the same thing when I was their age. But something is different now.\xe2\x80\x9d #Juneteenth'

b'Meet Shaquita. Shaquita Hill is a Risk Analyst Team Lead, based in Reno, NV. She looks to not only excel in her work, but to also contribute to making our workplace and our community a better place to be in. In her spare time, she enjoys yoga, hikes to waterfalls, and traveling!  #Juneteenth'

b'Meet Jazmine. My name is Jazmine Johnson and I am a Sales Consultant intern at Intuit. I am from Detroit, MI. I am a rising senior at the University of Michigan-Ann Arbor, where I attend the Stephen M. Ross School of Business. I am concentrating in Sales and Marketing with a minor in Entrepreneurship. I am very proud of my race and I hope to be a role model to other young African Americans from my community to diversify homogenous racial spaces, especially in corporate America. #Juneteenth'

b'Meet Milka. Milka Akinloye is a quadruple citizen of England, America, Nigeria, and Kenya. She shares that it is a daily tug of war to thrive with pride and reverence. Milka is based in the Intuit Fredericksburg office and works as an executive assistant for the sales team. #Juneteenth'

b'Meet Mos. Mos Okediji is a Learning and Development Coach for Global Marketing and Communications at Intuit. She\xe2\x80\x99s a Marketer turned learning and people development geek. She helps Marketers and Communicators thrive in their careers by connecting them to best in class coaching and resources. Personally, she\xe2\x80\x99s a wife, mom, and her life purpose is to be the champion of the underdogs so that they can thrive in their work and life.  #juneteenth'

b"Meet Melika. Melika Hope is the Head of Product Management for the Small Business & Self Employed Group at Intuit Canada, where she and her team build innovations to help business owners thrive and succeed. After studying classical piano and opera at Western University, she attended the Richard Ivey School of Business and received a degree in Business Administration. She worked at accounting firm RSM Richter for several years, where she gained her Chartered Accountant designation and led teams auditing companies primarily in the manufacturing and construction industries. She then pivoted to tech and product management at CaseWare International, before moving to manage the QuickBooks Online products at Intuit Canada. \nOutside of work, Melika likes to stay busy with a variety of passions and hobbies. She continues to play the piano and sings. She is a certified personal trainer and nutrition coach, and has a small part time business training clients in addition to competing in powerlifting at the national level. The daughter of an Antiguan immigrant and an 8th-generation Canadian, she has grown used to being the 'other' in different spaces and is a strong advocate for diversity and inclusion, particularly in professional environments.
